REQUIREMENTS - 8

LANGUAGE - DONE
Specify a language with the lang attribute on the <html> element on each .html page


CONTRAST - DONE
Ensure that the foreground text and background color of your site have sufficient contrast 
This will make your site more readable for everyone. 
Contrast Ratio is one tool for checking the contrast of your colors for both standard vision and color deficient user.
http://leaverou.github.io/contrast-ratio/


DOCUMENT STRUCTURE - DONE
Ensure heading elements i.e. <h1> are used to provide hierarchical structure to page content 
Specifically look for the <p> tags with the class "heading" these should be changed to help assist screen readers.


IMAGES - DONE (3 parts)
Text in banner area is part of the image and will not be picked up by screen readers. Use the background image without text (concert02_no_text.jpg) and add text to the HTML to roughly match the layout  - DONE
Add alt tags to images - DONE 
Make sure that the decorative images in tour.html have an empty alt attribute i.e alt="" - DONE (guitar pick images)


LINKS - DONE (3 parts)
Ensure links are visually distinct - DONE
Add hover state to links - DONE
Ensure the image link icons in the footer have accompanying text describing the link. 
However we don’t want to see this text on the page. Think about using alt text for the image - DONE 


TABLE - DONE  (2 parts)
Create a table for the tour dates information using the <td> element for table data cells and the <th> element for table header cells - DONE
Ensure your table has a scope and caption element - DONE


FORM - DONE (5 parts) 
Ensure form elements have styled focus states using the :focus pseudo class - DONE
Add associated labels for form controls - DONE 
Make sure all labels have a ‘for’ value. Matching for and id values associate the label with the appropriate form control - DONE 
Group form elements with a fieldset - DONE 
Add a legend to describe the grouping - DONE 
Ensure the select field options are in alphabetical order - DONE
Make sure you can select options in the drop-down menu by typing from the keyboard - Works with TAB, ENTER and UP/DOWN keys


CHECKING YOUR CODE - DONE (4 parts) 
Check Fangs extension for Firefox - DONE 
You can also copy and paste your HTML into the Accessibility Validator - DONE (index.html, survey.html, and tour.html passed)
You will also need to check your code against the Accessibility Checklist (see the Project Resources section for link) - DONE 
Check in Firefox, Edge, and Chrome - DONE 


EXTRA CREDIT: 
Add in aria landmark roles attributes to sections of the page. You will need to add in 3 per page - DONE

Use aria-describedby to add a description of what the submit form button does when clicked and to provide more information about parts of the form - DONE
